    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="275"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports, on reliable authority, that the edict agreeing to
                    450,000,000 taels as the amount of indemnity and 4 per cent as the rate of
                    interest was received in Peking on May 28.)</p>
            </div>
